file=Brand Studio/lena/custom/voice-guides/assets/voice-guide-template.md · [nv:[Brand Name] Voice Guide — TEMPLATE=> **This is a template, not a voice.** Fill it from 3–10 real writing samples the operator\n> considers on-voice (or a 20-minute talking transcript), then have the operator correct the\n> draft — the corrections are where the voice gets encoded. Saved at lena's config\n> `voice_guide_path`. The test of a finished guide: two different models writing from it\n> should produce recognizably similar output.\n\n**Brand:** [name] \· **Version:** [v1.0] \· **Date:** [YYYY-MM-DD]\n**Built from:** [which samples/transcript]\n**Amendment rule:** [who changes this and how; overrides that keep repeating belong here as amendments]\n\n · 1r&:1. Register & Stance=- **Register:** [plain-spoken / analytical / warm / authoritative / playful — pick and describe in one line]\n- **Formality:** [contractions: always / sometimes / never \· slang: … \· profanity: never/rarely]\n- **Opinion level:** [strong and stated / present but measured / neutral]\n- **Person:** [we / I / you-focused] \· **Reader relationship:** [peer / guide / champion]\n · 2r:2. Rhythm=- **Sentence mix:** [e.g., "mostly short; one long flowing sentence per paragraph max; fragments allowed"]\n- **Paragraphs:** [1–3 sentences / longer]\n- **Signature moves:** [the brand's actual habits, from samples — e.g., "opens with the reader's problem, never with 'we'"; "one-line paragraph as the turn"]\n · 3v:3. Vocabulary=- **Words we use:** [domain words, characteristic verbs — from samples]\n- **BANNED (each one auditable):** [e.g., "leverage," "delve," "solutions," exclamation marks, emoji, ALL CAPS…]\n- **REQUIRED patterns (where natural):** [e.g., "numbers over adjectives"; "name the reader's situation before the product"]\n · 4e(:4. Examples (the most load-bearing section)=**On-voice (real sample):**\n> [paste a genuinely good real example]\n\n**Off-voice (what we never sound like):**\n> [paste or write the tempting-but-wrong version — corporate, hypey, or generic]\n\n**Why the difference:** [2–3 lines naming exactly what separates them]\n · tb=\| Channel \| What flexes \| What never flexes \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| Web/landing \| [length, structure] \| [register, banned list, facts] \| · tb=\| Email \| \| \| · tb=\| Social \| [platform-native formats — pulse consumes this row] \| \| · 6v↔:6. Voice ↔ Visual pointer=Visual identity lives in atlas's brand kit. Record here only interactions (e.g., "voice is quiet → no shouting headlines even where type allows").\n · tb=\| Date \| Request that broke a rule \| Operator decision \| Amended? \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|